Probably oversharing… but if it helps anyone then worth it! 6 months ago I was at a pretty unhealthy weight. I say unhealthy because it’s not always just about looks - especially as you get older! I was really struggling to get the weight off post Covid. I tend to fluctuate a lot but this time was so different. As I’ve aged, I quickly found that the things that used to work for me weren’t working anymore. I was experiencing things I hadn’t before. It’s a pretty scary feeling. My metabolic age (the age your body and organs function like) was wayyy over my real age. Not good. 

One thing that seriously worried me was that because of my mom’s history of heart disease, I was at a greater risk of future health complications. 💔 My mom passed away at 54 due to a sudden massive heart attack, when I was just 23. Her health issues went undetected. Realizing that I’m not super far from my moms age when she passed… I realized I need to stay on top of my health especially after my most recent checkups pointed to an increase of the not-so-good things. 

Consulting with my doctors made me realize that it’s okay to have help to do something about it before it gets worse. Why wait? Because I plan on being around for my family much longer than my mom was. ❤️

This is not a paid ad, but I do want to thank @flexnowofficial for teaching me how to take control of my health and helping me add quality years to my life! Their Flex by Move 78 app is a game changer! 

Check out https://www.flexnow.care for more!

#weightloss #obesity #glp1 #wegovy  #metabolichealth #flexbymove78
#weightlossjourney #healthcoach
